moduleName: Gmail / Users / Settings / CSE / Identities / List
description: Lists the client-side encrypted identities for an authenticated user.

schema.description: OAuth 2 access token. Most APIs require `https://mail.google.com/` scope. Google Auth / Service Account Token can be used to obtain a valid access token.
API key can be generated in Google Developer Console in APIs & Services section. Leave blank if OAuth access token is used.
The requester's primary email address. To indicate the authenticated user, you can use the special value `me`.
The number of identities to return. If not provided, the page size will default to 20 entries.
Pagination token indicating which page of identities to return. If the token is not supplied, then the API will return the first page of results.
